  "body": "When trying to use kubectl from hyperkube I'm met with \"unknown flag\" errors. It looks as if the flags aren't being passed through to kubectl but hyperkube is trying to handle them itself (and subsequently giving an error when you give it flags it doesn't understand).\n\nYou can reproduce simply by running:\n\n```\ndocker run -it gcr.io/google_containers/hyperkube-amd64:v1.2.2 /hyperkube kubectl create -f x\n```\n\nAnd you'll see the error:\n\n```\nError: unknown shorthand flag: 'f' in -f\n\nKubernetes command line client\n\nUsage:\n  Kubernetes command line client [flags]\n\nAvailable Flags:\n..\n..\n..\n```\n",
